==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unisilicate
<hw>U`ni*sil"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets> + <ets>silicate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A salt of orthosilicic acid, <chform>H4SiO4</chform>; -- so called
because the ratio of the oxygen atoms united to the basic metals and
silicon respectively is 1:1; for example, <chform>Mg2SiO4</chform> or
2<chform>MgO.SiO2</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unison</ent>⟦br⟧
